Practice Lab (Commands to Run in Ubuntu VM)
Task 1 — View Running Processes
Run:
ps aux
Goal:View all running processes on the system.
Save output:
ps aux > process_list.txt

Task 2 — Find Specific Process
Find bash processes:
ps aux | grep bash
Explanation:
ps aux → shows processes
| → pipe output
grep bash → search for bash process

Task 3 — Monitor System Usage
Run:
top
Observe:CPU usage
Memory usage:running processes

Exit with:q

Task 4 — Install and Run htop
Install:sudo apt install htop
Run:htop

Explore:
process list
CPU usage
memory usage
Exit with:F10

Task 5 — Run Process in Background
Run:sleep 100 &

Explanation:
sleep 100 → wait 100 seconds
& → run process in background

Check jobs:
jobs
Example output:
[1]+ Running sleep 100 &

Task 6 — Bring Job to Foreground
Run:fg %1
Stop process:
CTRL + C
Task 7 — Kill a Process
Run process:sleep 500

Open another terminal and find it:
ps aux | grep sleep
Example output:ubuntu  2345 sleep 500
Kill process:
kill -9 2345


